text.section:
The court may order that restitution be paid to:
the victim;
the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene, the Criminal Injuries Compensation Board, or any other governmental unit;
a third-party payor, including:
an insurer; or
any other person that has, under Part I of this subtitle:
compensated the victim for a property or pecuniary loss; or
paid an expense on behalf of a victim;
any person for whom restitution is authorized by law; or
a person who has provided to or for a victim goods, property, or services for which restitution is authorized under § 11-603 of this subtitle.
